stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Migraines) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (What Is a Migraine?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (A migraine is a neurological event involving changes in brain chemistry, blood flow, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (nerve signaling. It typically involves moderate-severe headache plus other symptoms.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 614.4 Td (Migraine Phases) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 598.4 Td (- Prodrome \(hours-days before\): Mood changes, food cravings, neck stiffness, fatigue) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Aura \(20-60 min before, 25% of sufferers\): Visual disturbances, tingling, speech) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (difficulty) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Attack \(4-72 hours\): Throbbing head pain, nausea, light/sound sensitivity) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542.4 Td (- Postdrome \(hours-days after\): 'Migraine hangover' - fatigue, brain fog, weakness) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 512.6 Td (Types of Migraines) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 494.6 Td (- Migraine without aura \(most common, ~75%\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.6 Td (- Migraine with aura \(visual/sensory warning signs\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 466.6 Td (- Chronic migraine \(15+ headache days/month\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 452.6 Td (- Menstrual migraine \(linked to hormone changes\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.6 Td (- Vestibular migraine \(dizziness and balance issues\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 408.8 Td (Common Triggers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 390.8 Td (- Hormonal changes \(menstruation, ovulation\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 376.8 Td (- Stress \(or stress letdown - weekend/vacation\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 362.8 Td (- Sleep changes \(too much, too little, or irregular\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 348.8 Td (- Weather and barometric pressure changes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 334.8 Td (- Dietary triggers \(alcohol, aged cheese, MSG, nitrates\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 320.8 Td (- Dehydration and skipped meals) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 306.8 Td (- Sensory overload \(bright lights, strong smells, loud noise\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 292.8 Td (- Neck tension and poor posture) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
