80 0 obj
<< /Length 2675 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: Why are my migraines getting more frequent?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (Increased frequency can result from medication overuse, stress changes, hormonal shifts,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (new triggers, or progression to chronic migraine. Track patterns and discuss with your) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632.2 Td (neurologist.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 604.4 Td (Q: What is medication overuse headache?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (Using acute migraine medications more than 10-15 days per month can paradoxically cause) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (more headaches. If you need medication this often, discuss preventive options with your) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 560.4 Td (doctor.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 532.6 Td (Q: Can diet really help migraines?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 516.6 Td (For some people, yes. Common dietary triggers include alcohol, aged cheese, processed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 502.6 Td (meats, and MSG. An elimination approach can identify your personal triggers.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 474.8 Td (Q: Should I see a neurologist?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 458.8 Td (Consider a neurologist or headache specialist if: migraines are increasing, current) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 444.8 Td (treatment isn't working, you need acute medication 10+ days/month, or you have unusual) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 430.8 Td (symptoms.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 403.0 Td (Q: Are migraines dangerous?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 387.0 Td (While extremely painful and disabling, most migraines are not dangerous. However, always) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 373.0 Td (seek emergency care for sudden worst-ever headache, or migraine with neurological) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 359.0 Td (symptoms.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 331.2 Td (Q: Can exercise trigger migraines?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 315.2 Td (It can for some people, especially sudden intense exercise. Start gradually, warm up) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 301.2 Td (properly, stay hydrated, and exercise regularly rather than sporadically.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 273.4 Td (Q: What about caffeine?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 257.4 Td (Caffeine is complex for migraines - it can both trigger and treat them. Consistent) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 243.4 Td (moderate intake \(same amount daily\) is better than irregular use. Withdrawal is a common) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 229.4 Td (trigger.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 201.6 Td (Q: Do migraines get better with age?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 185.6 Td (Many people experience improvement after age 50-60, especially women after menopause.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 171.6 Td (However, this varies significantly between individuals.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
